# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Client Portal — Docker Compose overrides (repo root)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This file is ONLY consumed by `docker compose` for variable substitution in
# `docker-compose.yml` (compose auto-loads a `.env` file next to itself). It
# is separate from `backend/.env` and `frontend/.env`, which are read
# directly by the Node/Vite processes when you run each service without
# Docker (see the per-service `.env.example` files for those).
#
# Copy this file to `.env` at the repo root if you want to override any of
# the defaults baked into docker-compose.yml. Everything here is optional —
# `docker compose up` works out of the box without a root `.env`.

# --- Postgres credentials --------------------------------------------------
# Compose-level only: not read directly by any application code. The
# database name is fixed to `client_portal` per project convention and is
# not configurable here. The backend's DATABASE_URL is assembled from these
# two values automatically inside docker-compose.yml.
POSTGRES_USER=postgres
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=postgres

# --- Backend application vars (compose-only overrides) ---------------------
# These mirror backend/.env.example's defaults and are only used to override
# the values docker-compose.yml passes into the `backend` container — they
# do NOT affect `npm run dev` outside Docker (which reads backend/.env
# instead). Uncomment and set to override:
# CORS_ORIGIN=http://localhost:5173
# JWT_SECRET=change-me-to-a-long-random-string
# JWT_EXPIRES_IN=7d

# --- SMTP / Nodemailer (compose-only; enables real Gmail SMTP sending) -----
# Mirrors backend/.env.example. Left unset by default so the backend
# container omits SMTP_* entirely and keeps the log-and-skip dev default
# (see backend/src/config/env.ts). Uncomment and set all five to enable
# real sending via `docker compose up`:
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USER=your-gmail-address@gmail.com
# SMTP_PASS=your-gmail-app-password
# SMTP_FROM=Client Portal <no-reply@example.com>

# --- Seed script only (used by `docker compose exec backend npm run prisma:seed`) ---
# ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@example.com
# ADMIN_PASSWORD=ChangeMe123!
# ADMIN_NAME=Admin User
